						               													<description>A traditional quiz game in Swedish. M.I.G stands for Mobile Intelligence Games. It is very small and easy to play everywhere. A very good game to bring on a trip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two dice are rolled, one to decide category and one to decide if you have a 'M.I.G-chance' and the other decides in what category the question is. If the player didn't roll a 'M.I.G-chance' they have to answer the question correct to have another roll of the dice. If the player has a 'M.I.G-chanse' they have the opportunity to score, either way it's the next players turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to correctly answer a 'M.I.G-chance' in each category is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The questions come in 5 categories:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now &amp;amp; Then (Nu &amp;amp; d&amp;aring;)&amp;#10;Culture &amp;amp; Showbiz (N&amp;ouml;je &amp;amp; kultur)&amp;#10;Home &amp;amp; Away (N&amp;auml;r &amp;amp; Fj&amp;auml;rran)&amp;#10;Sports &amp;amp; All sorts (Sport &amp;amp; blandat)&amp;#10;Nature &amp;amp; Science (Natur &amp;amp; teknik)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game contains 312 cards with a total of 1560 questions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
